org.batfish.datamodel

Class PacketHeaderConstraints

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.datamodel.PacketHeaderConstraints

  • public class PacketHeaderConstraints
extends Object
    A set of constraints on an IPv4 packet header, where each field (i.e., constraint) is a Set of allowed values.
    • null values indicate no constraint.
    • Multiple values in a single set indicate a logical OR of multiple allowed values.
    • Different fields are ANDed together
    • Empty sets for a field will be rejected, as they imply a false value (i.e., nothing is allowed)

    Upon construction, the constraints are validated, although their intersections are not resolved. For resolution, see resolveIpProtocols(), and resolveDstPorts()
